<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbffa0e96-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16212"><num value="16212">§ 16212.</num><heading> High power density industry program</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbffa0e97-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16212/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall establish a comprehensive research, development, demonstration, and commercial application to improve the energy efficiency of high power density facilities, including data centers, server farms, and telecommunications facilities.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbffa0e98-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16212/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Technologies</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The program shall consider technologies that provide significant improvement in thermal controls, metering, load management, peak load reduction, or the efficient cooling of electronics.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idbffa0e99-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tIX/s922">Pub. L. 109–58, title IX, § 922</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/864">119 Stat. 864</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
